One year later and after a lot of personal struggles and a loss of a family member, my friend learns news that the judge rules against him and the case closes once and for all. An independent creator that got robbed off a multimillionaire corporation. The game project remains suspended in the fear of CBS / Netflix actually suing him dear to actually release the game, Anas’s career as an independent game developer, creator and artist remains uncertain and his right got totally lost in the process.

5 days ago, he filled an appeal to the ruling regarding this case. Having lost all rights, my friend needs a better defense team to help him win this moral fight against a hungry corporation that feeds off from ideas and doesn’t care about creativity, rights and ideals.

Gary Buechler, a famous YouTuber that runs Nerdrotic channel organized a fundraiser on GoFundMe and the support is immense. Before I’d know the whole issue, I couldn’t believe my eyes. The goal is almost reached in a span of few days but it’s not only that. My friend needs visibilty and attention from all people that love art - all artists that face the same problems of their work being uncredited. The US media tries so much to suppress the issue but we will do everything to let people know and support as they can.

Me, as a fellow creator and pixel artist, invite everyone on my page, artist or not, to share about this issue, help and support Anas. It may seem indifferent to you all but think of it as if it was you who got robbed off your creativity and human rights. What would you do?

#justiceforanas

[1/2] Hello friends, I don't do this usually but this goes for a very talented, kind-hearted person that needs all of our help, visibility and support, financial or not. Anas Abdin is a gifted independent creator and artist that draws melancholic vistas, nostalgic landscapes and space imagery in pixel fashion for years.

Back on May 2014 my friend started producing an indie-adventure point and click game named "Tardigrades" whose draft designs and videos were submitted onto Steam Greenlight later in November 2014. The game, which is still in production, takes place in 20000 BC where humanity discovers galactic travel through giant blue creatures called tardigrades and experiences the dawn of a new civilization on the galaxy. The game got the green light with later development being the only thing remaining before the release on Steam. 
On September 2017 CBS / Netflix released the first season of the sci-fi adventure Star Trek: Discovery. Set in the time between Star Trek: Enterprise and the original series, it explores the story of a crew that's entangled in an ongoing galactic war above a spaceship named Discovery. For several episodes, Discovery's drive operated through the aid of a giant blue tardigrade named "Ripper" which had lived symbiotically with the spore drive and it's connected with the drive's mycelial network which is a striking similarity to the game's use of giant blue tardigrades for intergalactic travel.

Furthermore, a lot of the show's mythology, character archetypes, visuals and locations have striking similarities with the game's respective elements. On October 2017, one month after the release of the show's first season, Anas posted about the issue on his blog and the following year attempted to work it out with CBS and address the issue but they just disrespected him by ignoring his allegations and postponed everything. On August 2018, my friend announced a lawsuit so the company would take him and his work seriously.
